Thank you, guys, for keeping our tradition alive this way.🖤

snippet.textDisplay: Bangladesh e folk song er moddhe onek valo valo content ase jekhane gaaner lyrics diye debor vabir moddhe flirtatious nature ke highlight or promote kora hoy nai. Personally ami mone kori debor er shathe vabir relation howa uchit ekta mutual respect er, not flirtatious. Otherwise that would negatively impact our social life and eta almost porokiyar porjaye pore jay! R jara “eita amader culture er part, so eikhane kisu bola jabe na” bole logic dibe tader jonno boli, apni jodi history te pichoner dike jete thaken apni ei vukhonde duniyar shob kisui paben jeta ke apnar culture hishebe dhore nite hobe, shotidah protha ke culture dhorte hobe, ballo bibaho ke culture dhorte hobe, women abuse ke culture dhorte hobe, perversion ke culture dhorte hobe, r o pichone gele wide spread homosexuality, nudity eishob ke culture dhorte hobe, caste system ke culture dhorte hobe, jomidari ke and gorib er upor ottachar ke culture dhorte hobe, ghetu system jekhane baccha cheleder jomidarra rape korto sheta ke culture dhorte hobe. Ogulo jodi apnar culture and history er ongsho howar poreo apnar modern mind er sense and morality er jonno suitable na hoy, then etao amar kase suitable na jekhane wife tar husband er choto vai er shathe ba vai tar vai er bou er shathe flirt korbe! As someone who has grown up in the twenty first centuries and in the urban areas of the country this is cringey and morally wrong to my modern mind. Jodi desher manusher shobar vabna and lifestyle e culture er part hoy, tahole amar and amar moto jara ei bepartar shathe agree koren na tader vabna o Bangla culture er part. On top of all these, the music doesn’t seem much appealing to me either! But then again I guess that’s different for everyone.
